'''Kazama clan''' (風間氏) is one of the {{ill|Clans in Japan|ja|日本の氏族|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Clans in Japan|qq=}}. According to legend, it originated in {{ill|979 AD|ja|979th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/979 AD|qq=}} during the {{ill|Tengen era|ja|天元 (日本)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tengen era|qq=}} when a branch of the {{ill|Suwa clan|ja|諏訪氏|1=Suwa clan|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa clan|qq=}}, dispatched to serve at {{ill|Kazama Shrine|ja|風間神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazama Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Province|qq=}} {{ill|Minochi District|ja|水内郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minochi District|qq=}}, adopted the surname Kazama. The clan is considered one of the {{ill|Jinke-to|ja|神家党|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jinke-to|qq=}}, a lineage of Shinto priest families.

== Niigata Prefecture ==
The Kazama clan became prominent as {{ill|Local lords|ja|土豪|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Local lords|qq=}} in {{ill|Echigo Province|ja|越後国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Echigo Province|qq=}}.
* They are said to trace their roots to {{ill|Kazama Shrine|ja|風間神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazama Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinano Province|qq=}}. According to legend, {{ill|Kazama Tachibano|ja|風間橘五|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazama Tachibano|qq=}} settled there while serving under {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinaka|ja|源義仲|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoshinaka|qq=}}, also known as Kiso Yoshinaka.{{Sfn|Ōta|1934|p=1457}}
* During the {{ill|Nanboku-chō period|ja|南北朝時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nanboku-chō period|qq=}}, Kazama Nobuaki, a {{ill|South Court (Japan)|ja|南朝 (日本)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/South Court (Japan)|qq=}} commander and Shinano Governor, fought valiantly under {{ill|Nitta Yoshisada|ja|新田義貞|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nitta Yoshisada|qq=}}, inflicting significant damage on the {{ill|North Court (Japan)|ja|北朝 (日本)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/North Court (Japan)|qq=}} and {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|足利尊氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga Takauji|qq=}}. He is said to have been a disciple of {{ill|Nichishō|ja|日昭|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nichishō|qq=}}, one of the {{ill|Six Elder Priests of Nichiren|ja|六老僧|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Six Elder Priests of Nichiren|qq=}}, and founded temples like {{ill|Hama Tsuchihokkeji|ja|浜土法華寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hama Tsuchihokkeji|qq=}} and {{ill|Murata Myōhōji|ja|妙法寺 (長岡市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murata Myōhōji|qq=}}.

=== Murakami ===
The Murakami branch of the Kazama clan originated in {{ill|Niitsu, Sawakami|ja|新津沢海|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Niitsu, Sawakami|qq=}} but later moved to {{ill|Murakami Domain|ja|村上藩|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murakami Domain|qq=}}, where they became prominent as textile merchants.

== Yamagata Prefecture ==
=== Sakata ===
In {{ill|1725 (Kyōhō 10)|ja|享保10th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1725 (Kyōhō 10)|qq=}}, the third head of the Murakami Kazama family, {{ill|Kazama Hikosō|ja|風間彦惣|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kazama Hikosō|qq=}}, moved to {{ill|Sakata|ja|酒田市|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sakata|qq=}}, marking the establishment of the Sakata Kazama lineage.

